      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POST PAINTER NZ (4) tackles the boys but was good against a strong field of mares in last week's Robin Dundee, finishing only 4.3m behind Eye Keep Smiling. Had been racing well with a string of wins and placings in Brisbane prior. This looks winnable. CLASSIC MISSION NZ (7) draws wider but has been racing well, getting close to the placegetters in handy line-ups in both outings since posting a win at this circuit and distance. Major player. BETTERTHANCASH NZ (1) was a bit disappointing when fading out last week but he is much better than that. Well served by the ace draw so could bounce back. GLITTER AINT GOLD (9) hasn't missed the top-four this time in, coming from a similar barrier to place here last time. Go well again. ALTA WILLIAM (3) looks close to a win off back-to-back placings here. Should get his chance from a good draw.",
